        \"rxn_018\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_019\": 0.97\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.86,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.91,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.9,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.95,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.9,\n      \"feedback\": \"This is one of the strongest routes. DAP-mediated phosphorylation is much better supported than generic orthophosphate phosphorylation, Ti-mineral-mediated adenosine formation is plausible, and the terminal acetyl phosphate/Fe3+ ATP formation is highly literature-aligned. The main residual issue is the weak free-ribose feeder branch.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_011\"\n      ],\n      \"suggestions\": [\n        \"Frame ribose production as a constrained, borate-stabilized minor route rather than robust output\",\n        \"Include explicit low-water-activity or paste conditions for DAP phosphorylation\",\n        \"If possible, replace free ribose with cyclic-phosphate or FaPy-like entry to improve realism\"\n      ]\n    },\n    {\n      \"pathway_id\": \"P6\",\n      \"reaction_scores\": {\n        \"rxn_008\": 0.93,\n        \"rxn_011\": 0.45,\n        \"rxn_015\": 0.9,\n        \"rxn_017\": 0.91,\n        \"rxn_018\": 0.84,\n        \"rxn_019\": 0.97\n      },\n      \"chemical_feasibility\": 0.87,\n      \"pathway_coherence\": 0.92,\n      \"environmental_progression\": 0.9,\n      \"target_achievement\": 0.95,\n      \"overall_confidence\": 0.91,\n      \"feedback\": \"Best overall pathway in the network. It combines a robust adenine source (formamide), selective mineral-mediated nucleoside formation, a well-supported DAP phosphorylation route, plausible cTMP-mediated AMP to ADP conversion, and the strongest known ATP-forming terminal step from ADP plus acetyl phosphate with Fe3+. The only significant weakness is the still-problematic free-ribose origin.\",\n      \"approved\": true,\n      \"problematic_reactions\": [\n        \"rxn_0